TITLE: Uber is making it easier to find your ride at the airport
SUMMARY: Uber on Tuesday unveiled some new product features that aim to make it easier for you to find your ride at the airport.
Dr. Marisa T. Cohen, a marriage and family therapist, created an AI chatbot boyfriend and reveals the details of the brief relationship.

TITLE: Twitter hit with one of the biggest outages since Elon Musk took over
SUMMARY: Twitter's website was inaccessible for many users on Monday while others reported issues seeing photos and clicking through links in the app, marking one of the most wide-ranging service disruptions to date under new owner Elon Musk.

TITLE: DOJ will hire more data experts to scrutinize digital monopolies, antitrust chief says
SUMMARY: The Justice Department will expand its stable of data experts charged with analyzing how businesses use and abuse consumer data to violate US antitrust law, the agency's antitrust chief told CNN in an onstage interview Monday.

TITLE: Verizon is raising prices on older cell phone plans
SUMMARY: Verizon is raising the prices on some of its older cell phone plans, the company confirmed to CNN on Monday. The move is part of a broader effort to get more of its customer base on 5G plans.

TITLE: Twitter users were unable to view tweets in latest service disruption under Musk
SUMMARY: Twitter's timeline page appeared to experience a prolonged outage on Wednesday morning, marking the latest service disruption for the platform under new owner Elon Musk.

TITLE: She was weeks away from maternity leave at Twitter. Then Elon Musk took over
SUMMARY: Bim Ali was early in her first pregnancy when billionaire Elon Musk agreed to buy Twitter, where she worked as a program manager on the Redbird core technologies team. During the months of intense uncertainty that followed, Ali stuck with the company, attempting to tune out the deluge of news about the on-again, off-again deal to focus on her health and the health of her child.

TITLE: Global chipmaking giant TSMC plans to hire 6,000 employees this year
SUMMARY: Semiconductor giant TSMC plans to add more than 6,000 jobs this year, despite a broader slowdown in demand for chips.

TITLE: Apple supplier Foxconn is on the hunt for semiconductor and EV deals in India
SUMMARY: Apple supplier Foxconn says it is seeking Indian partners to cooperate in areas such as chips and electric vehicles, as its chief executive wrapped up a visit to the country.

TITLE: Meta is cutting prices for its VR headsets
SUMMARY: Meta is cutting prices for two of its virtual reality headsets as it continues trying to boost adoption for the nascent technology on which it has bet its future.

TITLE: Facebook revamps controversial content moderation process for VIPs
SUMMARY: Facebook-parent Meta on Friday announced a revamp of its "cross-check" moderation system after facing criticism for giving VIPs special treatment by applying different review processes for VIP posts versus those from regular users.
See all of America's presidents sporting mullets. Who wears it best? CNN's Jeanne Moos reports.

TITLE: Amazon is pausing construction on its second headquarters in Virginia
SUMMARY: Amazon is pausing construction on its second headquarters in northern Virginia, the company confirmed in a statement to CNN on Friday.

TITLE: This game show app was an overnight sensation, and crashed just as fast
SUMMARY: When Scott Rogowsky auditioned to be the host of an unreleased online quiz show called HQ Trivia back in 2017, after a decade of grinding gigs in the New York City comedy scene, he didn't think it'd be his ticket to instant fame.

TITLE: GoodRx shared sensitive customer health information. Here's what happens next
SUMMARY: GoodRx customers who typically receive emails about prescription drug deals and refill reminders from the company saw something very different in their inboxes this week.

TITLE: Democratic senators urge Meta not to market its metaverse app to teens
SUMMARY: Two Democratic senators urged Meta this week to suspend a reported plan to offer Horizon Worlds, the company's flagship virtual reality app, to teens between the ages of 13 and 17, arguing the technology could harm young users' physical and mental health.
SpaceX and NASA launched a fresh crew of astronauts on a mission to the International Space Station, kicking off a roughly six-month stay in space.

TITLE: Alphabet's self-driving car unit has cut 8% of its staff this year
SUMMARY: Waymo, the self-driving car division of Google's parent company Alphabet, said on Wednesday that it has cut approximately 8% of its staff across two rounds of layoffs this year.

TITLE: Sen. Mike Lee says his personal Twitter account was suspended
SUMMARY: A personal Twitter account belonging to Utah Republican Sen. Mike Lee was suspended without warning or explanation, according to the senator.

TITLE: TikTok to set one-hour daily screen time limit by default for users under 18
SUMMARY: TikTok announced Wednesday that every user under 18 will soon have their accounts default to a one-hour daily screen time limit, in one of the most aggressive moves yet by a social media company to prevent teens from endlessly scrolling.
